# Event-Driven Rules (SQS FIFO — ADR-001)

## Event Structure (MUST follow exactly)
```java
// Base event — all domain events extend this
public record DomainEvent(
    String eventId,        // UUID string
    String eventType,      // "OrderCreated", "PaymentFailed"
    String aggregateId,    // domain entity ID
    String aggregateType,  // "Order", "Payment"
    Instant occurredAt,    // UTC
    String correlationId,  // trace ID for distributed tracing
    Object payload         // concrete event data
) {}

// Concrete event payload
public record OrderCreatedPayload(
    String orderId,
    String customerId,
    BigDecimal totalAmount,
    String currency,
    List<String> itemIds
) {}
```

## Publisher Pattern
```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class SqsOrderEventPublisher implements OrderEventPublisher {

    private final SqsAsyncClient sqsClient;
    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;

    @Value("${aws.sqs.order-events.url}")
    private String queueUrl;

    @Override
    public void publishOrderCreated(Order order) {
        DomainEvent event = new DomainEvent(
            UUID.randomUUID().toString(),
            "OrderCreated",
            order.getId().value(),
            "Order",
            Instant.now(),
            MDC.get("traceId"),
            new OrderCreatedPayload(...)
        );
        sendToSqs(event, order.getId().value()); // messageGroupId = aggregateId for FIFO
    }

    private void sendToSqs(DomainEvent event, String messageGroupId) {
        try {
            sqsClient.sendMessage(SendMessageRequest.builder()
                .queueUrl(queueUrl)
                .messageBody(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(event))
                .messageGroupId(messageGroupId)
                .messageDeduplicationId(event.eventId())
                .build());
        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {
            throw new EventPublishingException("Failed to serialize event", e);
        }
    }
}
```

## Consumer Pattern
```java
@SqsListener("${aws.sqs.order-events.url}")
public void handleOrderCreated(String message) {
    try {
        DomainEvent event = objectMapper.readValue(message, DomainEvent.class);
        MDC.put("traceId", event.correlationId());  // propagate trace
        // delegate to application service
        notificationService.handleOrderCreated(event);
    } catch (Exception e) {
        log.error("Failed to process event: {}", message, e);
        throw e; // rethrow → SQS dead-letter queue
    } finally {
        MDC.clear();
    }
}
```

## Rules
- `messageGroupId` MUST equal `aggregateId` (guarantees FIFO per entity)
- `messageDeduplicationId` MUST equal `eventId` (idempotent delivery)
- Consumer MUST rethrow on failure → goes to DLQ (dead-letter queue)
- NEVER change existing event field names — add new fields only
- NEVER delete event fields without a deprecation period of ≥ 1 release

## Checklist before PR
- [ ] Event has all 7 required base fields
- [ ] Publisher uses `aggregateId` as `messageGroupId`
- [ ] Publisher uses `eventId` as `messageDeduplicationId`
- [ ] Consumer propagates `correlationId` to MDC
- [ ] Consumer rethrows on failure (DLQ path)
- [ ] No breaking change to existing event schema
